## Summary

The `magicbell-js` v1.7.0 user-client API provides a `Client` class that accepts an `SdkConfig` with a `token` property (the User JWT). The `Client` exposes a `channels` property of type `ChannelsService`, which has a `saveUserPreferences(body: UserPreferences)` method that sends a `PUT` request to `/channels/user_preferences`.

---

## 1. Import Path

```typescript
import { Client } from 'magicbell-js/user-client';
```

The package.json `exports` map confirms this subpath export resolves to `./dist/esm/user-client.d.ts` (for ESM) or `./dist/commonjs/user-client.d.ts` (for CJS).

**Also exported from the same module** (useful for types):
```typescript
import { Client, Environment, UserPreferences, Categories, Channels } from 'magicbell-js/user-client';
```

---

## 2. Client Initialization with User JWT

